<% @title = "Rates, Schedule and Ferry Information" %>
<% @description = "Get Washington Island Ferry information, schedules and rates for unique ferry trips to Door County's Washington Island in beautiful northeast Wisconsin." %>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">

    <div class="col-md-12">
      <div class="page-intro">
        <h1>The Ferry to Washington Island...</h1>
        <h2>Ferry Rates, Schedule and Information.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-12">
      <div class="main-content" id="main">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-8 center-block">
            <h1>Washington Island Ferry Schedule</h1>
            <%= render 'shared/search_form' %>
            <%= render 'search_results' %>
            <p class="text-center"><%= link_to "2018 printable schedule", '/downloads/washington-island-ferry-schedule-2018.pdf', :target => "_blank" %></p>
            <p class="text-center caption">Ferry schedule is subject to change due to weather and traffic.</p>
            <hr>
          </div>

          <div class="col-md-8">

            <div class="visible-xs visible-sm">
              <%= render "shared/washington_island_ferry_rates" %>
              <hr>
            </div>

            <p>At the tip of the Door County peninsula, you’ll find Northport Pier and the Washington Island Ferry Line to Washington Island. The island is a 35-square mile, year-round home to 700 people and a destination for thousands of visitors annually. The Washington Island Ferry Line is a vital, year round transportation link, crossing Death’s Door passage on the way to the island.</p>
            <p>Start your journey today!</p>

            <hr>

            <h2>Driving Directions</h2>
            <p>The ferry to Washington Island is located on the tip of the Door Peninsula, in the Northeast corner of Wisconsin. Take Highway 57 North from Green Bay to Sturgeon Bay. From there, you can take either Hwy 42 or Hwy 57 to Sister Bay. Then, follow Hwy 42 to its end at Northport Pier.</p>
            <iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d179661.42421914704!2d-87.08142584617839!3d45.28398299402334!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4d4d18e4d182ea0d%3A0xe3e1ba339daffd24!2sNorthport+Pier!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1426627096285" width="100%" height="350" frameborder="0" style="border:0"></iframe>

            <hr>

            <h2>Please Remember:</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Be at the dock and in line at least 15 minutes before scheduled departure. (Schedule may be subject to weather and traffic.)</li>
              <li>We are not responsible for low exhaust systems.</li>
              <li>Tickets are sold on a first-come-first-served basis.</li>
              <li>Pets must remain in a car and must be on a leash if on the car deck.</li>
              <li>There is no smoking on board the ferry.</li>
            </ul>

            <hr>

            <h2>Rock Island</h2>
            <p>Interested in visiting Rock Island State Park? You will need to take a second, passenger-only ferry, the Karfi, from Washington Island to Rock Island. Schedule and rates for the Karfi Ferry are available on our <a href="/rock-island-ferry">Rock Island</a> page.</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-green btn-lg" href="/rock-island-ferry">Rock Island Ferry Schedule</a></p>
          </div>

          <div class="col-md-4 hidden-xs hidden-sm">
            <%= render "shared/washington_island_ferry_rates" %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
